python revision day 5

if statement should end with :
if statement not need elif and else part all  the time

interpreting time:
.py programs change to byte codes

running time or run time(execution time):
byte code convert to binary code

input()

input function use for get inputs from user when the run time.
we can give a string value in input function arguement.
example:
name=input("please enter your name")

in runtime output;
please enter your name
notes:
if user enter kumar,kumar stored in name variable
in runtime user give any value, the value store as string data type.
whenever programer need a integer value from user,programer use type casting.(ex)
mark=int(input("please enter your mark"))
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
type()

type()_function use for check the data type of a value.

mark=80
print(type(mark))

output:
class int
