nested if statements:

age=int(input("please enter your age")
nationality=input("please enter your nationality")
if age >5:
	if nationality.lower()=="indian":
		print("your eligible for aadhar")
	else:
		print("not for other nationalities')
else:
	print("age criteria not met")
	
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2 conditions in if statement:

age=int(input("please enter your age"))	
if age > 5:
    nationality=input("enter your nationality")
    if nationality=="indian" or nationality== "INDIAN":
    	print("your eligible for aadhar")
    else:
        print("not for other nationalities")
else:
    print("age criteria not met")

== ----> equals to
!= ----> not equals to

if not using in a program:

if not and != are same


age=int(input("please enter your age"))	
if age > 5:
    nationality=input("enter your nationality")
    if not nationality.upper()=="INDIAN"
    	print("not for other nationalities")
    else:
        print("you are eligible for aadhar")
else:
    print("age criteria not met")

